<TITLE> Taiwan leader sees daily China flights in 6 months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TAIPEI, Nov 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Taiwan President Ma Ying-jeou said on Tuesday the island would likely launch direct flights with China in about half a year, signaling closer trade ties between the two political rivals. Ma made the comments in a speech at a business event. Taiwan and China signed an agreement earlier this month to allow regular direct flights on weekends, although it still needs the approval of Taiwan's parliament to be implemented
